 <div class="title" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">ACCVI vulnerability equations</div>
 <p id="Par66" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The additive Eq. 
  <a rid="Equ9" ref-type="" href="#Equ9">9</a> is a raw version of the original vulnerability equation which defines how vulnerability is numerically calculated (as described in Eq. 
  <a rid="Equ1" ref-type="" href="#Equ1">1</a>). Eq. 
  <a rid="Equ8" ref-type="" href="#Equ8">8</a> is a multiplicative version of Eq. 
  <a rid="Equ9" ref-type="" href="#Equ9">9</a> which has been used in similar frameworks assessing climate change vulnerability indices at large scales
  <span class="sup">
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR44" href="#CR44">44</a>,
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR45" href="#CR45">45</a>,
   <a ref-type="bibr" rid="CR76" href="#CR76">76</a>
  </span>. The multiplicative version assumes that exposure and sensitivity create an impact, and one unit of this impact can be offset by one unit of adaptive capacity.
 </p>
